The paper discusses optimization and properties of consensus clustering, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining. The focus on optimization suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of mathematical theorems and proofs suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The applications of consensus clustering to various tasks, such as constructing profiles and motifs, suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the use of statistical measures and analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
